&lt;td&gt;CVE-2020-1472&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Netlogon Elevation of Privilege Vulnerability&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists when an attacker establishes a vulnerable Netlogon secure channel connection to a domain controller, using the Netlogon Remote Protocol (MS-NRPC). An attacker who successfully exploited the vulnerability could run a specially crafted application on a device on the network.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cHM6Ly9wb3J0YWwubXNyYy5taWNyb3NvZnQuY29tL2VuLVVTL3NlY3VyaXR5LWd1aWRhbmNlL2Fkdmlzb3J5L0NWRS0yMDIwLTE0NzI=&#34;&gt;https://portal.msrc.microsoft.com/en-US/security-guidance/advisory/CVE-2020-1472&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
